						<summary>

						<p>This inscription refers to the sacred services undertaken in the temple of Seṅgaṇmalīśvaramuḍaiyār at Taiyūr in Iraṇḍāyiravēlippaṟṟu at Kumiḻi nāḍu, a sub-division of Āmūr kōṭṭam by a certain Muttuvālu śeṭṭi, son of Paraśurāma śeṭṭi of Cheṉṉapaṭṭaṇam.</p>						

						</summary>
